Dear Students,


Greetings from MIT School of Holistic Development (SHD), MIT ADT University, Pune!


We take this opportunity to congratulate you on completing the previous academic year successfully and embarking upon the journey of the next academic year.


You will be glad to know that in this academic year, you have an opportunity to learn a foreign language. We offer French, German, Japanese and Spanish as electives under the foreign language course which is spread over two semesters. To help you decide which language is the most suitable for you from your career point of view, we have organised an online compulsory orientation session.


We are writing to invite you to the "Orientation Session on SHD Foreign Language courses", organised exclusively for you by the Department of Foreign Languages, MIT SHD for all the third-year students of MIT Art, Design & Technology University (2nd/4th year students in case of IOD and SOA, respectively). 


The details of the orientation programme are given below  

*Day and Date -* Friday, 14th July 2023
*Time -* 03:00 pm
*Venue -* Online (Zoom registration link - https://bit.ly/FLOrientationSession14thJuly)
*Agenda -* Presentations by the FL faculty followed by a Q&A session


Kindly register for the session and attend it on time. (The live session will also be available later on our Facebook page  https://www.facebook.com/mitsohdpune/)


This session will help you to familiarize yourselves with various aspects of the Foreign Language courses, hence helping you to choose an elective thoughtfully. The event poster has been attached with this email for your reference. 


We look forward to having you all for the virtual session.


Thank you.


With best wishes,




*Team Foreign Languages &*
*Dr. Atul Patil*
*Director*
*MIT School of Holistic Development*
*MIT ADT University*

Dear Students, 
An engagement program "Prose & Code" with Josh Software has been scheduled as follows  Date  24th July 2023
Day  Monday
Time  11:00 am
Location Raj Kapoor Auditorium 

All the TY and LY CSE  students are requested to present for the engagement program.

WHAT IS PROSE & CODE?

Prose & Code is a platform to share knowledge that matters, and effectively delivered through short talks and presentations by industry Subject Matter Experts. 

Dialogue with experts provides students with alternative perspectives, opinions, and personal experiences. This helps develop multiple skills like critical thinking, reasoning, planning and be future ready. 

WHY PROSE & CODE?
A combination like yin & yang, beauty & the beast has always had a perfect recipe for success, likewise, Prose & Code gives the audience a combination of Non-tech & Technical learning opportunities to develop holistically and become more aware of the focused concepts or ideas that the presenter concentrates on.

The main difference between K-Means and K-Medoids is that K-Means uses the mean of the data points as the cluster center, while K-Medoids uses one of the data points as the cluster center. This means that K-Means can produce clusters with different shapes and sizes, but it is more sensitive to outliers and noise. K-Medoids, on the other hand, can produce clusters with more compact and spherical shapes, but it is less sensitive to outliers and noise. ¬π‚Å¥

Both algorithms use k-means algorithm because they are based on the same principle of minimizing the distance between each data point and its cluster center. However, they differ in how they choose the cluster centers. K-Means uses a random initialization of k centroids, then assigns each data point to the closest centroid, and updates the centroids by taking the mean of their assigned points. K-Medoids uses a greedy approach of selecting k data points as medoids (or exemplars), then assigns each data point to the closest medoid, and updates the medoids by replacing them with their assigned points.
